<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-268-619  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 268 619.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Jan 9 1989 n520 p14(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Export flow may grow; science panel: ease 'commodity' controls.andO;(National Academy of Sciences recommendations)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The National Academy of Sciences (NAS) has issued recommendationsthat could dramatically change US computer-technology exportpolicies.andP;  The report, requested by the State Department,acknowledges the 'commoditization' of products such asmicrocomputers and related software.andP;  It recommended that exportcontrols should be lifted in trade to CoCom (CoordinatingCommittee for Multilateral Export Control) countries.andP;  It alsorecommended that specialized products such as supercomputers,which can be used for military purposes, be monitored closely.andO;The report is expected to have a major impact at the CommerceDepartment and the Pentagon, where previous NAS reports havecaused significant changes in policy._National Academy of SciencesandM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ExportInternational TradeCommoditiesNational Academy of SciencesGovernment Regulation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>